===Etymology===
From ''[[air]]'' + ''[[craft]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=aircraft}}

# A [[machine]] capable of atmospheric [[flight]] due to interaction with the [[air]], such as [[buoyancy]] or [[lift]].
# {{plural of|[[aircraft]]}}

====Usage notes====
*The word ''aircraft'' is a [[Appendix:Glossary#countable|countable]] noun, but with the same plural form as singular; hence "one aircraft", "two aircraft", etc.
*When the term ''aircraft'' is used without qualification, it is not usually taken to include [[rocket aircraft]].

